Skijumpdesign is released under an open source license and managed with Gitlab
to encourage reuse and contributions. Questions about the software should be
directed to the authors via email or as an issue posted to:

http://gitlab.com/moorepants/skijumpdesign/issues

Instructions on how to submit an issue via Gitlab are found here:

https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/project/issues/create_new_issue.html

We accept proposals for software bug fixes, feature additions, documentation
improvements, etc via the Gitlab merge request system:

http://gitlab.com/moorepants/skijumpdesign/merge_requests

Instructions on how to submit a merge request via Gitlab are found here:

https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/gitlab-basics/add-merge-request.html

The software authors will review your submissions, provide feedback, and accept
if it is deemed appropriate. It is best to raise an issue for discussion prior
to work on large additions and changes.
